title: The Iwakura Embassy some chapters
description:
From 1871 to 1873 to Empire of Japan sent its first official embassy (althought unofficial travel by Japaneses converted to Christianity existed in the past), lead by nobleman Iwakura, to explore the Western world from America to Europe, in order to learn more about European culture and civilization.
One of the members, historian Kunitake Kume, wrote a series of books relating their journey.

Every chapter is in single pdf file. List of chapters is in chapter_list.txt

Enjoy
